50|$|Their {{first feature}} {{documentary}} <b>The</b> <b>Linguists</b> follows two linguists, Gregory Anderson and David Harrison, as they circle the globe attempting to record dying languages. The film received a positive review from Boston Globe reviewer Sam Allis. <b>The</b> <b>Linguists</b> premiered at <b>the</b> 2008 Sundance Film Festival before airing nationwide on PBS in February 2009. It {{was nominated for}} an Emmy Award for Outstanding Science and Technology Programming in 2010.|$|R
