25|$|In 2006, <b>the</b> <b>linguist</b> Robert Blust, {{proposed}} that the Sama-Bajaw languages derived from the Barito lexical region, though not from any established group. It is thus a sister group to other Barito languages like Dayak and Malagasy. It is classified under the Bornean geographic group.|$|E
